modules.description: Handles parsing and evaluation of OCaml expressions in a REPL environment, supporting type checking and error reporting. Operates on abstract syntax trees, input strings, and evaluation contexts. Used for implementing interactive OCaml sessions and real-time code validation.

Provides directory navigation and printer installation for toplevel environments. Operates on strings, formatatters, and long identifiers. Enables dynamic loading of modules and custom pretty-printing in interactive OCaml sessions.
